&lt;h3&gt;Notes - Slide 8&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Which allows us to describe &lt;a href="https://code.research.uts.edu.au/MIF/microscope-instructions/wikis/Nikon-Ti/Nikon-Ti-inverted-epifluorescent-microscope"&gt;individual items of equipment&lt;/a&gt; ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href="https://www.isi.edu/~carl/"&gt;Carl Kesselman&lt;/a&gt; said at the workshop:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why isn't &lt;a href="https://www.force11.org/group/fairgroup/fairprinciples"&gt;FAIR&lt;/a&gt; important when you take it off the microscope?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Evenhuis at UTS thinks the same way. He is doing stuff because it is the &lt;strong&gt;right&lt;/strong&gt; thing to do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;hr/&gt;
&lt;section typeof='http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/Slide'&gt;
